OL,3,CHS2 independent review launched in bid
OL,4,Cto get 'spiralling costs' back on track
OL,6,FTo achieve this, the Government is
OL,7,Falso reinstating ministerial oversight
OL,8,Fof the project to ensure greater
OL,9,Faccountability. This will see regular
OL,10,Fmeetings starting immediately, where
OL,11,Fboth the Transport Secretary and Rail
OL,12,FMinister, Lord Hendy, alongside the
OL,13,FChief Secretary to the Treasury, will
OL,14,Fchallenge delivery and remove
OL,15,Fobstacles to securing the full
OL,16,Fbenefits of the railway more cost
OL,17,Feffectively.
OL,19,FNorthern cities will 'remain poorly
OL,20,Fserved' by rail after axing of HS2,
OL,21,FGovernment advisers warn
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
